    "reasoning": "# Analysis\n\n## (a) Time left until resolution\n\nThe 2026 Nobel Peace Prize will be announced in October 2026. Today is July 3, 2026. Approximately **3 months** remain until the announcement.\n\n## (b) Status quo outcome if nothing changes\n\nThe 2026 Nobel Peace Prize will be awarded to some laureate(s), and ERRs will not be among them. The prize goes to a different organization or individual. This is the default outcome.\n\n## (c) Scenario for NO outcome\n\nThe Norwegian Nobel Committee selects a laureate from among the 287 candidates (208 individuals, 79 organizations) and does not include ERRs. Given that ERRs do not appear on the 2026 Polymarket as of late January 2026, and given typical market behavior reflects informed expectations, the market has essentially priced them out.\n\n## (d) Scenario for YES outcome\n\nThe Norwegian Nobel Committee, recognizing ERRs' humanitarian work serving 11.5+ million people and their receipt of two prestigious alternative peace/human rights awards (Rafto Prize, Right Livelihood Award), decides to award or co-award the 2026 Nobel Peace Prize to ERRs despite their absence from betting markets and despite losing out in 2025 when they were front-runners.\n\n## (e) Base rate\n\nThe background provides:\n- Historical data: The PRIO Director's shortlist \"has correctly identified the winner in 10 of 12 years since 2014\" \u2014 accuracy rate of ~83%.\n- Historical precedent on alternative prizes: Four Rafto Prize winners later won Nobel Peace Prize (Aung San Suu Kyi, Kim Dae-jung, Shirin Ebadi, Jose Ramos-Horta).\n- The prize is shared sometimes, and the committee selects from ~287 candidates.\n\nRough base rate: If ~1 in 287 candidates wins (and some years multiple entities share), the simple base rate for any given organization is roughly 0.3\u20130.5% per year. However, organizations that have won alternative prizes and are on expert shortlists have substantially elevated odds.\n\n## (f) How live data/research/background moves from base rate\n\n**Major headwind:** ERRs do not appear on the 2026 Polymarket betting market as of late January 2026. This is a sharp signal that:\n- Informed bettors, after ERRs reached 33% odds in 2025, have repriced them downward.\n- The market is forward-looking and has apparently concluded ERRs are unlikely in 2026.\n- No 2026 PRIO shortlist announcement appears in the research/background provided.\n\n**Supporting factors:**\n- ERRs won two major alternative prizes (Rafto, Right Livelihood) in 2025, elevating their profile.\n- Historical precedent exists for Rafto winners later winning Nobel Peace Prize.\n- ERRs' humanitarian impact (11.5M+ people served, 735 rooms, 26K volunteers) is substantial and documented.\n\n**Complicating factor:**\n- They were front-runners in 2025 and *lost*. The Committee may have decided they were not the right fit for 2025, which could reduce their odds in 2026.\n- Their absence from betting markets despite 2025 prominence suggests market participants do not expect them to win in 2026.\n\n## (g) How view has changed since original 2% forecast\n\nThe original forecast (2% as of ~31 days ago, around early June 2026) appears to have been based on:\n- Their 2025 prominence but failure to win.\n- Absence from 2026 betting markets.\n- General difficulty of repeating or accelerating peace prize recognition within a single organization in consecutive years.\n\n**Current view:** The original 2% was reasonably calibrated. The evidence has not substantially changed since then:\n- No 2026 PRIO shortlist has been published yet (as far as the research indicates).\n- Market remains quiet on ERRs for 2026.\n- They are still serving millions but have not come into fresh prominence beyond their 2025 awards.\n\nI would not move significantly from 2%, but given the Rafto Prize precedent (4 of those winners later won Nobel), modest recognition of that track record might suggest 2\u20134% rather than 1\u20132%.\n\n## (h) Community prediction\n\nNo community prediction is provided in the prompt. If Metaculus has a forecast, it is not shared here.\n\n---\n\n## Reasoning Summary\n\nERRs are experiencing a post-award lull. They were hot in 2025 (33% odds, top PRIO shortlist), yet the Committee chose Maria Corina Machado. In 2026, there is no evidence of:\n- Betting market interest (they're absent from Polymarket).\n- A fresh PRIO shortlist announcement naming them prominently.\n- Breaking news that would re-elevate their profile.\n\nThe historical fact that some Rafto Prize winners (4 documented cases) later won Nobel Peace Prize is noteworthy, but these winners typically won within 0\u20133 years of their Rafto prize. ERRs winning in 2026, one year after Rafto and immediately after a 2025 near-miss, would require either:\n1. The Committee to reconsider them with new urgency, or\n2. A major escalation in their work or in Sudan's geopolitical significance that generates fresh Nobel-worthiness.\n\nNeither appears evident in the provided research.\n\n**Calibration:** A 2\u20133% probability reflects:\n- Very low baseline odds (~0.3\u20130.5% for a random candidate).\n- Uplifted somewhat for their 2025 awards, documented impact, and Rafto precedent.\n- Heavily discounted for their 2025 loss and absence from 2026 betting markets.\n\nGiven the original 2% forecast and the lack of material new evidence since early June 2026, I will stay close to that estimate, perhaps creeping to 2.5% to acknowledge the Rafto Prize precedent.\n\n**Probability: 2.5%**",
    "research_text": "I've reviewed the summary carefully for internal contradictions regarding metrics, indices, counts, dates, and time periods.\n\n**Finding:** No contradictions detected.\n\nAll figures are either:\n- Attributed to specific, non-conflicting dates (March 2026 for the shortlist announcement; mid-June for betting odds; October 9th for the announcement date)\n- Stated without temporal qualifiers in ways that don't contradict other statements (287 candidates, 208 individuals, 79 organisations)\n- Consistent across mentions (ERRs' 2025 awards are listed once; their leading betting position is noted once with a specific date range)\n\nThe summary is internally consistent.\n\n---\n\n**Return: UNCHANGED**",
